race.comment: New Mick Travers acquisition MENZAH ONE (2) ran a better race last start at the second run of the campaign, closing well to finish third over this distance at Canberra in a Class 1. Tested at stakes level last prep under the McEvoys in Adelaide. Has his share of weight but with further improvement might be too good for these. LIGHT FOOT (3) worked home well without threatening first-up over 1175m at Albury. Led all the way to win at this stage last prep over today's course and distance. Has a nice sense of timing about this appearance. ASTUNNER (1) has thrived under new mentor Darrell Burnet this prep. Great effort to be beaten just a length in a BM74 over 1200m at Wagga Riverside most recently. Big weight to contend with but should run well again. JASKIER (8) continued his good recent form with a close fourth over 1200m at Echuca last start. Is a winner at this trip and looks sure to be thereabouts again. TYCOON ARTIE (4) can improve third-up over an extra 100m.
